# Tooling

All linting, formatting, and type-checking runs through **pre-commit hooks** defined in `.pre-commit-config.yaml`. Do not add duplicate npm scripts for these concerns.

## Hooks and what they cover

| Hook | Tool | Scope |
|------|------|-------|
| `prettier` | Formatting | JS, TS, TSX, SCSS, CSS, JSON, HTML |
| `eslint` | Linting | JS, TS, TSX |
| `stylelint` | CSS linting | SCSS, CSS |
| `tsc` | Type-checking | `apps/web` TypeScript |
| `markdownlint-cli2` | Markdown linting | All `.md` files |
| `ruff-check` / `ruff-format` | Python linting + formatting | `pipeline/` only |
| `trailing-whitespace`, `end-of-file-fixer`, etc. | File hygiene | All files |

## Running checks

```bash
# Run all hooks against all files
pnpm check

# Run a single hook by id
pre-commit run eslint --all-files
pre-commit run tsc --all-files
pre-commit run stylelint --all-files
```

Hooks also run automatically on `git commit`.

## Config files

- `.pre-commit-config.yaml` — hook definitions
- `eslint.config.js` — ESLint rules
- `.stylelintrc.json` — Stylelint rules
- `.prettierrc.json` — Prettier rules
- `.markdownlint.yaml` — Markdownlint rules
